    <p>Age­ing well</p>
    <p>Some peo­ple seem to age very quickly, and look older than their age, while oth­ers age less rapidly. Keep­ing age­ing at bay for as long as pos­si­ble will al­low us to en­joy our later years in good health as age­ing is the largest risk fac­tor for many chronic con­di­tions such as car­dio­vas­cu­lar dis­ease. With this in mind, ST senior health correspond­ent Joyce Teo speaks with Pro­fes­sor Brian Kennedy, di­rec­tor of the NUHS Cen­tre for Healthy Longevity, on what we can do to de­lay age­ing.</p>

